          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Six Targets of Isotopically Pure U-238, Each with a",
                "Thickness of Approximately 1.5 Mg/Cm**2 Mounted in",
                "Sandwich on Aluminum Backings 0.1 mm Thick, were Used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".The Hauser-Feschbach Model."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "STRUC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The Disposition Lomg- And Short-Lived Isomers",
                "Of 235-Np. Authors Believe That Ground State of 236-Np",
                "Is the Long-Lived One."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "CYCLO"
                ],
                "institute": "2SF ABA"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BCINT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "STTA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "It was Necessary to Take Into Account the Fact That not",
                "Only 236-Pu But Also 238-Pu from the Reaction",
                "238-U(P,N)238-Np-->238-Pu Accumulated in the Target.",
                "Because of the Considerable Thickness of the Uranium",
                "Targets (1.5 MILLIGRAMM/CM**2), It was Impossible to",
                "Resolve the 236-Pu and 238-Pu Peaks in the Alpha",
                "Spectra. The Relative Ratio of the Activity of the",
                "Plutonium Isotopes was Obtained by Measuring the Alpha",
                "Spectra of the Aluminum Foils Separaiting the Uranium",
                "Targets During Proton Irradiation. This Method Made It",
                "Possible to Measure the Reaction Cross Sections of Both",
                "238-U(P,N)238-Np and 238-U(P,3N)236-Np-Short-Lived."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CRITIQUE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The Energies of 238-Np and 236-Np Nuclei are not Equal.",
                "Therefore the Ranges of Residuals are Different. It was",
                "Not Excluded That the Ratio 238-Np/236-Np on Aluminum",
                "Foil will not be Equal this Ratio in Uranium Target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SOLST"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ".A Surface-Barrier Silicon Detector to Detect",
                "Alpha-Particles."
              ]
            }
          ],
